Object oriented programming

1. Real world actors <-> Data in the software
  - Objects
    - RAM at some random memory address
    - Student objects in the RAM - 10 objects
    - Professor objects in the RAM - 20 objects
  - class
    - Helps in the creation of an object
    - 1 to n objects using a class
    - Gives a data type to an object
    - Blueprint for an object

2. Real world actor characteristics <-> Properties of the objects in the RAM

3. Real world actor actions <-> Methods to be called on the object

Constructors